WEBVTT

1
00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:12.781
This is a routine pursuit.

2
00:01:12.948 --> 00:01:17.202
Main Force repeats,
this is a routine pursuit. Code 44.

3
00:01:17.744 --> 00:01:19.246
Listen, you tell them we need some help.

4
00:01:19.496 --> 00:01:21.540
This should be
an open-code blitz and you know it.

5
00:01:21.707 --> 00:01:23.208
- You have your information.
- Good one.

6
00:01:23.709 --> 00:01:25.627
Come on, sweetheart,
this one's a heavyweight!

7
00:01:26.128 --> 00:01:27.671
Main Force repeats,
you have your information.

8
00:01:27.838 --> 00:01:28.755
Okay.

9
00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:32.134
This is a routine pursuit.
Please liaise with Big Bopper.

10
00:01:33.385 --> 00:01:35.721
March Hare to Big Bopper.
Assist on Code Three Red Alert.

11
00:01:36.305 --> 00:01:38.307
March Hare to Big Bopper.
March Hare to Big Bopper.

12
00:01:39.057 --> 00:01:40.892
Big Bopper. Got you, Hare.
What's going down?

13
00:01:41.268 --> 00:01:42.227
We've got a cop-killer.

14
00:01:43.312 --> 00:01:44.062
You're kidding!

15
00:01:44.563 --> 00:01:46.940
Be warned, Saree, this is non-compliance.

16
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:49.693
The Main Force will
not tolerate such action.

17
00:01:52.613 --> 00:01:55.407
This pursuit is designated
a standard Code 44.

18
00:01:56.241 --> 00:01:58.368
Please respond only to that code.

19
00:01:59.036 --> 00:02:01.830
Code 44 indicates no requirement
for a blockade.

20
00:02:02.581 --> 00:02:04.499
A Pursuit Special has been stolen.

21
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:08.670
Hall Captain Fifi Macaffee
doesn’t like this any more than you.

22
00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:12.424
However, we must not compromise
territorial range.

23
00:02:12.841 --> 00:02:15.719
Remember that only by
following instructions

24
00:02:15.886 --> 00:02:18.930
can we hope to maintain
a successful highway program.

25
00:02:19.931 --> 00:02:22.059
Oh, Jesus, March Hare to Big Bopper.

26
00:02:22.309 --> 00:02:24.603
We're around three minutes off
the intersection. Reckon you'll make it?

27
00:02:25.187 --> 00:02:27.022
- We'll make it! Move over!
- No!

28
00:02:27.564 --> 00:02:28.398
I'm driving!

29
00:02:29.191 --> 00:02:30.984
Not this again! I've been assigned!

30
00:02:33.612 --> 00:02:37.866
Hang on. I'm supposed
to drive this crate! Darn you.

31
00:02:39.451 --> 00:02:40.202
Go on.

32
00:02:41.703 --> 00:02:43.455
Hey, Saree, what's the form on this thing?

33
00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:45.999
A twisto bikey, scoot jockey.

34
00:02:46.458 --> 00:02:48.627
A few hours ago, down in Sun City,
he goes berserk.

35
00:02:49.044 --> 00:02:50.837
Breaks custody, wastes a young premmie,

36
00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:52.297
and takes off in a Pursuit Special.

37
00:02:53.006 --> 00:02:54.091
We've been on him ever since.

38
00:02:55.008 --> 00:02:56.385
This one's right up the air, Roop.

39
00:02:56.927 --> 00:02:59.388
I've seen the style before.
Terminal psychotic.

40
00:03:07.145 --> 00:03:07.813
What's he driving?

41
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:10.357
That's what hurts. It's one of our V8s.

42
00:03:10.941 --> 00:03:13.151
Pursuit Special on methane. Very toey!

43
00:03:22.536 --> 00:03:24.246
Okay, we're about a half mile
off Anarchie Road.

44
00:03:24.413 --> 00:03:25.372
You'll see him any minute now.

45
00:03:30.085 --> 00:03:32.546
Rip the guts out of it.
Give it the bejesus!

46
00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:38.927
See him yet?

47
00:03:39.761 --> 00:03:40.470
Got it!

48
00:03:42.431 --> 00:03:43.765
I'm gonna blow him away!

49
00:03:45.475 --> 00:03:47.394
I'm gonna ram him! I'm gonna ram him!

50
00:04:08.457 --> 00:04:09.583
Hey, fellas, you okay?

51
00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:13.712
Acknowledge, Big Bopper, acknowledge.
Are you okay?

52
00:04:15.130 --> 00:04:16.047
Roop, Charlie.

53
00:04:16.631 --> 00:04:18.800
Do you see me, Toecutter?

54
00:04:19.301 --> 00:04:21.344
Do you see me, man?

55
00:04:24.139 --> 00:04:27.225
Keep going, keep going, we're okay.

56
00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:29.227
We got you, we're going.

57
00:04:34.107 --> 00:04:36.276
Born with a steering wheel in his hand

58
00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:37.944
<i>and lead in his foot.</i>

59
00:04:38.153 --> 00:04:41.239
He is the Nightrider

60
00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:45.118
cruising at the speed of fright!

61
00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:50.332
This is the Nightrider,
and we ain't never coming back!

62
00:04:52.542 --> 00:04:56.087
I'm a fuel-injected suicide machine!

63
00:04:57.380 --> 00:05:00.008
I am a rocker! I am a roller!

64
00:05:01.426 --> 00:05:02.385
I think we're still mobile.

65
00:05:03.178 --> 00:05:05.055
For Christ's sake, shove over!

66
00:05:05.555 --> 00:05:06.640
You're blaspheming again.

67
00:05:07.390 --> 00:05:08.975
I don't have to work with a blasphemer.

68
00:05:12.354 --> 00:05:14.773
I am the Nightrider!

69
00:05:22.906 --> 00:05:25.784
Big Bopper to March Hare.
We're still in the game, okay?

70
00:05:26.409 --> 00:05:27.369
Understand this.

71
00:05:27.828 --> 00:05:29.830
That scag and his floozy,

72
00:05:30.872 --> 00:05:31.706
they're gonna die!

73
00:05:37.254 --> 00:05:40.215
Main Force to Gosling One.
Main Force to Gosling One.

74
00:05:40.715 --> 00:05:43.718
Code 44, standard pursuit. Please respond.

75
00:05:43.885 --> 00:05:45.387
MFP to Gosling One.

76
00:05:46.805 --> 00:05:48.098
Main Force to Gosling One.

77
00:05:49.182 --> 00:05:50.308
It was all slow motion.

78
00:05:50.642 --> 00:05:52.519
He leaves his seat and
goes through the windscreen,

79
00:05:52.894 --> 00:05:54.521
headfirst straight into the tree, right?

80
00:05:55.105 --> 00:05:56.898
And then bounces back
through the windscreen.

81
00:05:59.568 --> 00:06:02.571
And by the time we got to him,
he was just sitting there

82
00:06:02.737 --> 00:06:04.406
trying to scream with his face ripped off.

83
00:06:07.993 --> 00:06:08.577
What's the matter?

84
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:10.328
Not hungry, am I?

85
00:06:11.329 --> 00:06:12.205
Give it here.

86
00:06:13.623 --> 00:06:14.207
I'll tell you what...

87
00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:15.083
God, look at that.

88
00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:18.503
- Christ!
- Strewth, at it again.

89
00:06:19.921 --> 00:06:20.839
Catch you later, Goose.

90
00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:50.869
Christ, they're heading for population!

91
00:07:07.469 --> 00:07:08.887
Now, what's this I hear
about you and Jonathan?

92
00:07:09.679 --> 00:07:10.680
What about Jonathan?

93
00:07:10.847 --> 00:07:12.265
You were seen out with him two nights ago.

94
00:07:12.641 --> 00:07:13.475
So what?

95
00:07:17.479 --> 00:07:19.022
It's this way.

96
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:38.917
He's gone.

97
00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:40.043
Bastards!

98
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:43.254
Shit!

99
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:45.340
We're really gonna get it this time.

100
00:07:45.507 --> 00:07:46.508
He had his indicator on.

101
00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:47.801
Shut up!

102
00:07:51.972 --> 00:07:55.308
No, no! You're not going on.
Stay off the road!

103
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:57.227
Of course, I'm going on. Shut up!

104
00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:58.895
<i>People's lives are in peril!</i>

105
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:02.607
Stay off the roads!

106
00:08:05.694 --> 00:08:08.279
I'm gonna have him. I'm gonna have him!

107
00:08:08.446 --> 00:08:09.030
You're in peril!

108
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.159
Stay off the roads!

109
00:08:15.578 --> 00:08:16.329
Get off the road!

110
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.248
- I've got him! Shut up! Shut up!
- Stay off the roads!

111
00:08:29.718 --> 00:08:30.343
Oh, my God.

112
00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:34.597
Watch out!

113
00:08:45.525 --> 00:08:46.693
That was a close one!

114
00:08:53.074 --> 00:08:53.908
I am ready.

115
00:08:54.576 --> 00:08:56.161
I am ready for your best.

116
00:08:58.079 --> 00:08:58.872
Oh, my God, what's happened?

117
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:01.499
I don't know, man. I just got here meself.

118
00:09:03.168 --> 00:09:04.252
I think he broke his leg.

119
00:09:04.669 --> 00:09:06.129
I want to find out what's happening.

120
00:09:07.172 --> 00:09:08.214
Hey, Max, can you hear me?

121
00:09:08.381 --> 00:09:09.549
Main Force Patrol,

122
00:09:10.425 --> 00:09:13.511
we're out of the game,
unable to continue pursuit.

123
00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:16.056
You'd better send a meat truck.

124
00:09:16.347 --> 00:09:17.932
Charlie's copped a saucer in the throat.

125
00:09:18.141 --> 00:09:18.975
Hey, Max?

126
00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:22.353
Hey, Max?

127
00:09:22.729 --> 00:09:23.480
Go ahead.

128
00:09:24.314 --> 00:09:26.983
We are 100 percent SNAFUed.

129
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:27.901
You okay?

130
00:09:28.526 --> 00:09:30.570
Nothing a year in the tropics
wouldn't fix.

131
00:09:31.321 --> 00:09:31.988
Much damage?

132
00:09:35.033 --> 00:09:37.035
You should see the damage, Bronze, huh?

133
00:09:38.328 --> 00:09:39.162
Metal damage,

134
00:09:39.621 --> 00:09:40.413
brain damage, huh?

135
00:09:40.580 --> 00:09:41.748
Are you listening, Bronze?

136
00:09:42.248 --> 00:09:44.751
I am the Nightrider!

137
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:50.465
I'm a fuel-injected suicide machine.

138
00:09:50.965 --> 00:09:53.843
I am a rocker! I am a roller!

139
00:09:54.260 --> 00:09:56.846
I am an out-of-controller!

140
00:09:57.013 --> 00:09:57.972
Whoo!

141
00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:00.642
I am the Nightrider, baby,

142
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:05.230
<i>and it's me and Marmaduke,
and we ain't never coming back.</i>

143
00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:25.250
The Toecutter, he knows who I am.

144
00:10:26.042 --> 00:10:28.169
I am the Nightrider!

145
00:10:34.551 --> 00:10:38.346
I am the chosen one,
the mighty hand of vengeance

146
00:10:38.596 --> 00:10:41.057
sent down to strike the unroadworthy!

147
00:10:42.934 --> 00:10:45.520
I'm hotter than a rolling dice.

148
00:10:45.687 --> 00:10:46.896
Step right up, chum,

149
00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:52.026
and watch the kid lay down a rubber road
right to freedom!

150
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:32.233
What's wrong?

151
00:11:36.112 --> 00:11:37.197
Baby, what's wrong?

152
00:11:49.792 --> 00:11:52.086
It's going...
It's going and...

153
00:11:52.795 --> 00:11:55.173
there'll be nothing left. It's all gone.

154
00:12:03.556 --> 00:12:04.599
Stop!

155
00:13:03.866 --> 00:13:05.618
Oh. That feels good.

156
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:09.497
After three days, that feels so good.

157
00:13:12.917 --> 00:13:14.919
I got a right hook
in the mouth this morning.

158
00:13:15.086 --> 00:13:16.087
- Sprog?
- Mm-hm.

159
00:13:16.671 --> 00:13:18.923
I told him to always lead with his left.

160
00:13:19.590 --> 00:13:21.926
You know, I think we've got
a monster on our hands.

161
00:13:22.093 --> 00:13:24.512
Yeah, takes after his old man.

162
00:13:24.846 --> 00:13:25.638
What's that?

163
00:13:26.347 --> 00:13:27.223
Monster!

164
00:13:29.225 --> 00:13:31.728
Montazano, who called
himself the Nightrider,

165
00:13:31.978 --> 00:13:35.148
had broken from custody
and escaped in the police vehicle.

166
00:13:35.648 --> 00:13:36.983
- You made the news again.
- Mmm-hmm.

167
00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:39.444
He was awaiting arraignment on charges
relating to the slaying of a Main Force...

168
00:13:39.610 --> 00:13:40.862
- Who was he?
- Don't know.

169
00:13:41.029 --> 00:13:42.822
...Patrol officer in a road blockade
accident last month.

170
00:13:43.156 --> 00:13:44.574
Just another glory rider, I guess.

171
00:13:44.907 --> 00:13:48.453
...episode in the Sun City sectors
in the past 27 days.

172
00:14:10.475 --> 00:14:11.768
Jessie, I told you.

173
00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:14.103
The Goose wants me there early.

174
00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:15.396
What for, he didn't say.

175
00:14:15.688 --> 00:14:16.689
You know the Goose.

176
00:14:18.399 --> 00:14:18.983
Coffee's ready.

177
00:14:43.925 --> 00:14:45.259
I'm not grumpy.

178
00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:53.434
Get out of here.

179
00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:57.980
Okay.

180
00:14:59.065 --> 00:14:59.816
Gotta go.

181
00:15:11.536 --> 00:15:12.120
Oi!

182
00:15:23.339 --> 00:15:24.048
What's that?

183
00:15:26.342 --> 00:15:27.343
Crazy about you.

184
00:15:46.529 --> 00:15:49.991
All supplies must be requisitioned
from the people's bond.

185
00:15:50.741 --> 00:15:53.453
Please do not exploit your privileges.

186
00:15:53.703 --> 00:15:55.413
Doing so is an offense.

187
00:15:56.247 --> 00:15:57.415
Memorandum Seven:

188
00:15:57.915 --> 00:16:00.793
The Captains of the Hall have
asked that pursuit officers

189
00:16:00.960 --> 00:16:05.298
refrain from using the slang "Bronze"”
for the Main Force Patrol.

190
00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:07.884
The word is considered disrespectful

191
00:16:08.050 --> 00:16:11.345
and citizens should be actively
discouraged from its use.

192
00:16:14.765 --> 00:16:16.142
Memorandum Eight:

193
00:16:16.767 --> 00:16:18.978
Hospital vouchers
are available again.

194
00:16:19.395 --> 00:16:23.316
MFP personnel may sign on with
the following sector captains.

195
00:16:23.733 --> 00:16:28.112
One, six-three, two-four, one-one-two,

196
00:16:28.279 --> 00:16:30.490
five-seven and two-six.

197
00:16:32.074 --> 00:16:33.326
Kick it in the guts, Barry.

198
00:16:38.915 --> 00:16:41.083
She's the last of the V8s.

199
00:16:41.959 --> 00:16:43.461
You can shut the gate on this one, Max.

200
00:16:43.628 --> 00:16:44.670
It's the duck's guts.

201
00:16:44.837 --> 00:16:46.297
Yeah, she's the last of the V8s.

202
00:16:46.464 --> 00:16:47.924
She sucks nitro.

203
00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:49.550
Phase four head.

204
00:16:49.926 --> 00:16:51.511
- Twin overhead cam.
- Tell him about the blower, yeah?

205
00:16:51.677 --> 00:16:53.471
600 horsepower through the wheel.

206
00:16:54.055 --> 00:16:54.972
The blower, the blower.

207
00:16:55.139 --> 00:16:58.684
Oh, she's meanness put to music
and the bitch is born to run.

208
00:16:59.936 --> 00:17:01.354
He's in a coma, man!

209
00:17:01.521 --> 00:17:02.438
He loves it.

210
00:17:13.366 --> 00:17:13.991
Okay.

211
00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:17.453
How the hell did you
get all this together?

212
00:17:18.871 --> 00:17:21.249
It just happened, Max, you know?

213
00:17:21.499 --> 00:17:24.043
Piece from here and a piece from there.

214
00:17:24.627 --> 00:17:26.170
- So easy?
- Yeah.

215
00:17:27.338 --> 00:17:29.257
Come on, Max. You--you've seen it.

216
00:17:29.423 --> 00:17:30.383
You've heard it

217
00:17:31.342 --> 00:17:32.969
and you're still asking questions.

218
00:17:37.098 --> 00:17:38.641
When do we go for a ride?

219
00:17:42.395 --> 00:17:43.271
He loves it.

220
00:17:45.064 --> 00:17:45.940
I think we've got him.

221
00:17:46.190 --> 00:17:47.108
I hope so.

222
00:17:47.942 --> 00:17:48.859
Yeah, we've got him.

223
00:17:49.402 --> 00:17:51.237
Your top pursuit man
wanted to quit the road

224
00:17:51.404 --> 00:17:53.406
and we have to seduce him with candy?

225
00:17:54.407 --> 00:17:56.909
<i>People don't believe in heroes anymore.</i>

226
00:17:57.326 --> 00:18:00.246
I know, Macaffee.
You want to give them back their heroes.

227
00:18:01.497 --> 00:18:02.999
You will not try this one on me again.

228
00:18:03.332 --> 00:18:05.251
I do not enjoy wasting money.

229
00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:06.168
Goodbye

230
00:18:07.587 --> 00:18:08.421
and good luck!

231
00:18:10.256 --> 00:18:11.507
Thanks, Labatouche.

232
00:18:12.592 --> 00:18:13.843
You're a real human being.

233
00:18:42.121 --> 00:18:43.122
Get out of my way!

234
00:18:43.456 --> 00:18:44.915
The old meat grinder's
humming tonight, huh?

235
00:18:45.082 --> 00:18:47.793
Yeah, Max took out a couple of crazies
over the high side.

236
00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:52.340
Will you shut up!

237
00:18:54.008 --> 00:18:55.384
The hot mops and the towees.

238
00:18:58.095 --> 00:18:58.929
It's in the food.

239
00:18:59.305 --> 00:19:00.973
Hey, Max, another one for your books, eh?

240
00:19:01.682 --> 00:19:02.475
Hey, you eaten yet?

241
00:19:02.642 --> 00:19:04.560
No, not yet. I'll pick up something later.

242
00:19:04.727 --> 00:19:07.980
Hey, that Code Three you ran down
a few days ago, the, uh...

243
00:19:08.147 --> 00:19:09.315
- Nightrider?
- The Nightrider, yeah.

244
00:19:09.482 --> 00:19:10.983
- Uh, I've got a problem.
- What's that?

245
00:19:11.150 --> 00:19:13.110
Well, his friends.
Word's out they're out to get you.

246
00:19:13.569 --> 00:19:15.196
- Scoot jockeys?
- Yeah, nomad trash.

247
00:19:15.363 --> 00:19:18.157
Mm. Well, I'll add it
to my threat collection.

248
00:19:19.241 --> 00:19:20.701
Good boy, Max. You're a good boy.

249
00:19:20.868 --> 00:19:22.036
- Hey.
- Hey!

250
00:19:22.411 --> 00:19:23.037
Come on.

251
00:21:20.863 --> 00:21:22.114
Good afternoon.

252
00:21:23.407 --> 00:21:24.283
Good afternoon.

253
00:21:25.409 --> 00:21:26.911
We're here to meet a friend.

254
00:21:27.203 --> 00:21:28.370
Come in on the train.

255
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:31.707
Nothing come in on the train
except a couple of crates and a...

256
00:21:33.876 --> 00:21:34.460
coffin.

257
00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:37.254
Our friend.

258
00:21:38.839 --> 00:21:40.508
You'll have to see the agent
and sign the papers.

259
00:21:42.301 --> 00:21:45.095
