Here I am, trying to put sense to it

523
00:50:09.048 --> 00:50:10.216
when I know there isn't any.

524
00:50:15.471 --> 00:50:17.431
I'll be all right,
once I get it clear in my head.

525
00:50:41.497 --> 00:50:42.164
Fif.

526
00:50:43.999 --> 00:50:44.583
Fif.

527
00:50:48.379 --> 00:50:49.004
What's this?

528
00:50:49.505 --> 00:50:50.089
I'm through.

529
00:50:50.839 --> 00:50:52.216
- Again?
- No, not again.

530
00:50:52.383 --> 00:50:53.717
I'm through. I'm quitting.

531
00:50:53.968 --> 00:50:54.635
Sit down.

532
00:50:54.969 --> 00:50:56.387
No, I didn't come here to discuss it,

533
00:50:56.554 --> 00:50:58.514
I came to say it. I'm through.

534
00:50:59.265 --> 00:51:00.349
Now, just a minute!

535
00:51:02.560 --> 00:51:04.270
All right, so the Goose bought it.

536
00:51:04.687 --> 00:51:06.105
But that's the way
he always came at the world.

537
00:51:06.272 --> 00:51:06.855
Off beat.

538
00:51:07.606 --> 00:51:10.359
Max, you'd be the first
to admit it was long overdue.

539
00:51:12.027 --> 00:51:13.737
All right, I'll tell you how it is.

540
00:51:14.280 --> 00:51:15.489
You're a winner, Max.

541
00:51:16.240 --> 00:51:17.533
You're on the top shelf

542
00:51:18.075 --> 00:51:18.909
and I'm not gonna lose you

543
00:51:19.076 --> 00:51:21.120
because of some crazy notion
about quitting!

544
00:51:24.164 --> 00:51:27.418
They say people don't believe
in heroes anymore.

545
00:51:28.586 --> 00:51:29.545
Well, damn them!

546
00:51:30.170 --> 00:51:31.505
You and me, Max,

547
00:51:32.881 --> 00:51:35.342
we're gonna give them back their heroes.

548
00:51:35.634 --> 00:51:39.263
Fif...do you really expect me
to go for that crap?

549
00:51:40.139 --> 00:51:42.016
You gotta admit,
I sounded good there for a minute, huh?

550
00:51:42.182 --> 00:51:43.100
Yeah.

551
00:51:43.684 --> 00:51:44.351
Bye, Fifi.

552
00:51:45.144 --> 00:51:47.646
Hey! Hey, come on, do you want me to beg?

553
00:51:48.856 --> 00:51:50.482
Do you want me on my knees, crying?

554
00:51:52.026 --> 00:51:53.235
Now just a minute.

555
00:51:54.153 --> 00:51:55.404
Give me a reason.

556
00:51:59.658 --> 00:52:00.701
I'm scared, Fif.

557
00:52:02.244 --> 00:52:03.037
Do you know why?

558
00:52:03.454 --> 00:52:04.997
It's that rat circus out there.

559
00:52:05.831 --> 00:52:06.832
I'm beginning to enjoy it.

560
00:52:06.999 --> 00:52:08.542
What is this, funny week?

561
00:52:08.709 --> 00:52:11.378
Look, any longer out on that road,
and I'm one of them, you know?

562
00:52:11.795 --> 00:52:13.172
A terminal crazy.

563
00:52:13.922 --> 00:52:16.800
Only I've got a bronze badge
to say I'm one of the good guys.

564
00:52:17.217 --> 00:52:18.552
You know what I'm trying to say?

565
00:52:20.512 --> 00:52:21.639
I'll tell you what I'll do.

566
00:52:27.227 --> 00:52:28.646
Take off a few weeks, huh?

567
00:52:29.980 --> 00:52:31.482
Grow yourself a beard.

568
00:52:32.483 --> 00:52:34.735
Draw flies.
Just think about it for a while.

569
00:52:35.694 --> 00:52:38.113
If you still feel the same way
when you come back, it's okay by me.

570
00:52:39.114 --> 00:52:39.782
Go on.

571
00:52:45.913 --> 00:52:46.955
I'm not gonna change my mind.

572
00:52:47.748 --> 00:52:49.792
Get out of here
before I decide to come with you, huh?

573
00:52:51.877 --> 00:52:54.171
Bye, Fif. Thank you.

574
00:52:58.217 --> 00:52:59.968
You'll be back, Rockatansky!

575
00:53:01.303 --> 00:53:02.680
You're hooked, Max.

576
00:53:03.722 --> 00:53:04.723
And you know it!

577
00:54:10.706 --> 00:54:15.169
I've never been able to say things to you,
Jess, about how I feel.

578
00:54:17.629 --> 00:54:19.715
Guess I always counted on
you understanding.

579
00:54:28.056 --> 00:54:28.974
When I was a kid,

580
00:54:30.476 --> 00:54:34.521
me and my father
used to go for long walks.

581
00:54:36.982 --> 00:54:39.067
I remember staring down at his shoes.

582
00:54:41.028 --> 00:54:43.906
They were special shoes, brown.

583
00:54:45.115 --> 00:54:47.284
And he always kept them really shiny.

584
00:54:50.204 --> 00:54:54.333
He was tall,
and he used to take long strides.

585
00:54:55.834 --> 00:54:57.628
And there I'd be right alongside him

586
00:54:58.796 --> 00:55:00.214
just trying to keep up with him.

587
00:55:04.802 --> 00:55:09.139
I don't think he ever knew
how proud I felt of him.

588
00:55:11.475 --> 00:55:13.977
Or how good it felt
just to be there alongside him.

589
00:55:17.523 --> 00:55:19.817
Even now, when I think back on it,
I still feel...

590
00:55:24.947 --> 00:55:26.114
The thing is, Jess,

591
00:55:28.575 --> 00:55:30.077
I couldn't tell him about it then,

592
00:55:30.786 --> 00:55:32.454
but I can tell you about it now.

593
00:55:36.375 --> 00:55:37.668
I don't wanna wait 10 years

594
00:55:37.835 --> 00:55:39.211
to tell you how I'm feeling
about you right now.

595
00:55:39.378 --> 00:55:39.962
Do you know...

596
00:56:06.989 --> 00:56:07.573
Hello.

597
00:56:08.156 --> 00:56:08.991
Get a load of that!

598
00:56:09.157 --> 00:56:10.701
Yeah, we had a blowout a while back.

599
00:56:10.868 --> 00:56:12.202
Raunchy, very raunchy.

600
00:56:13.412 --> 00:56:14.204
What's the donk like?

601
00:56:14.371 --> 00:56:16.331
Yeah, the donk's fine.
Look, about this tire...

602
00:56:17.332 --> 00:56:18.667
Don't do much work on these meself,

603
00:56:18.834 --> 00:56:20.377
except to scrape them off the road.

604
00:56:21.086 --> 00:56:23.213
Yeah. Hey, how about this tire, huh?

605
00:56:23.380 --> 00:56:24.590
Have it fixed in no time.

606
00:56:24.756 --> 00:56:26.675
I can sell you a set of "lops
for next to nothing.

607
00:56:26.925 --> 00:56:27.634
No, thanks.

608
00:56:27.801 --> 00:56:29.261
I can't remember where I got 'em,

609
00:56:29.595 --> 00:56:30.971
but I got 'em, know what I mean?

610
00:56:31.138 --> 00:56:34.224
No, we'll be all right
just as soon as we get this fixed.

611
00:56:34.850 --> 00:56:35.893
- Max?
- Yeah?

612
00:56:37.769 --> 00:56:38.353
Listen,

613
00:56:39.730 --> 00:56:42.733
Sproggo's talked me into
buying him an ice cream, so, uh,

614
00:56:43.317 --> 00:56:44.401
I think I'll see you later.

615
00:56:45.277 --> 00:56:47.821
Sure, there's a shop just down the beach.

616
00:56:48.405 --> 00:56:49.865
They'll appreciate the business.

617
00:56:50.324 --> 00:56:51.575
Sure, thanks.

618
00:56:52.659 --> 00:56:53.285
Toodlepip.

619
00:57:08.175 --> 00:57:09.593
- You just trucking around?
- Yeah.

620
00:57:09.843 --> 00:57:11.345
- Good time for just trucking.
- Mm.

621
00:57:11.595 --> 00:57:12.930
Wish I could do a bit meself.

622
00:57:13.347 --> 00:57:14.681
Which way you heading? North?

623
00:57:14.848 --> 00:57:15.599
Uh, maybe.

624
00:57:46.171 --> 00:57:48.340
Look what's turned up for Sunday dinner.

625
00:57:49.633 --> 00:57:52.302
Main course and dessert.

626
00:57:53.136 --> 00:57:54.638
My favorite kind.

627
00:57:55.722 --> 00:57:56.640
Female.

628
00:58:11.863 --> 00:58:13.657
Puss, puss, puss, puss, puss.

629
00:58:22.290 --> 00:58:22.958
Hey, you.

630
00:58:28.630 --> 00:58:29.214
Hey, whoa.

631
00:58:36.847 --> 00:58:38.056
Watch the tongue, lovable.

632
00:58:38.223 --> 00:58:40.392
I've seen him lick his own eyebrow clean.

633
00:59:12.340 --> 00:59:15.135
That's not cheaply done.
You must've spent some coin.

634
00:59:15.469 --> 00:59:18.472
Like the sign says,
speed's just a question of money.

635
00:59:18.972 --> 00:59:20.390
How fast do you wanna go?

636
00:59:21.308 --> 00:59:22.768
- Max, quick, get in.
- What's wrong?

637
00:59:23.018 --> 00:59:24.644
Look, just take my word for it, get in!

638
00:59:24.811 --> 00:59:25.729
What about the tire?

639
00:59:25.896 --> 00:59:27.064
Please, Max!

640
00:59:29.816 --> 00:59:31.109
Hey, your tire, man.

641
00:59:32.527 --> 00:59:34.988
Hey, fella, what about your tire?

642
00:59:38.784 --> 00:59:39.868
Crazy people, man.

643
00:59:41.828 --> 00:59:43.163
The world's full of crazy people.

644
01:00:00.931 --> 01:00:02.015
- That wagon.
- Yeah?

645
01:00:02.182 --> 01:00:02.766
Was it here?

646
01:00:02.933 --> 01:00:05.685
Sure, sure, a couple with a kid.
I was just fixing their tire.

647
01:00:06.144 --> 01:00:07.938
They left their goddamn spare.
Not a bad one either.

648
01:00:10.774 --> 01:00:11.525
Who are they?

649
01:00:11.691 --> 01:00:14.277
A couple, passing through.

650
01:00:14.444 --> 01:00:16.530
Said they were heading north. Maybe.

651
01:00:29.501 --> 01:00:31.128
You want to drive the car? Yeah?

652
01:00:31.711 --> 01:00:33.088
Well, you can't anymore.

653
01:00:33.421 --> 01:00:34.256
Into the back.

654
01:00:34.506 --> 01:00:35.340
Here you go.

655
01:00:37.968 --> 01:00:39.594
I can still see his face now.

656
01:00:40.095 --> 01:00:41.721
Looked as if he'd just swallowed a brick.

657
01:00:41.888 --> 01:00:44.307
What a mean old lady you are. Huh, boss?

658
01:00:45.183 --> 01:00:47.018
That's enough from you, mate! Enough.

659
01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:54.025
What's the matter with you?

660
01:00:58.530 --> 01:00:59.781
What you got there, mate?

661
01:01:04.077 --> 01:01:05.078
Max!

662
01:01:10.167 --> 01:01:13.295
Yup. Yeah, that's the way I see it, too.

663
01:01:14.713 --> 01:01:15.839
Eh. Yeah.

664
01:01:16.631 --> 01:01:19.217
Yep, sure.
Sure, it's been nice talking to you. Bye.

665
01:01:21.303 --> 01:01:22.387
Take it you agreed with him.

666
01:01:22.971 --> 01:01:24.222
They aren't worried, I'm not worried.

667
01:01:24.389 --> 01:01:25.265
And what about that?

668
01:01:27.851 --> 01:01:28.977
I figure it's lost property.

669
01:01:29.561 --> 01:01:32.522
If no one makes a claim to it,
I say we can forget it.

670
01:01:34.816 --> 01:01:35.984
Sounds okay to me, Jess.

671
01:01:36.651 --> 01:01:37.402
Don't know.

672
01:01:38.320 --> 01:01:40.989
If Ziggy says so, believe me, it's okay.

673
01:01:41.907 --> 01:01:43.617
May's expecting you
up at the farm sometime.

674
01:01:44.784 --> 01:01:45.785
You'll have no trouble up there.

675
01:01:46.286 --> 01:01:47.412
Just green grass.

676
01:02:21.905 --> 01:02:22.572
How are you doing?

677
01:02:22.989 --> 01:02:24.991
Mm. I'm getting there.

678
01:02:32.415 --> 01:02:36.503
I reckon you ought to connect
the doohickey to the gizmo.

679
01:02:39.464 --> 01:02:40.131
Come here, you.

680
01:02:40.548 --> 01:02:44.261
Oh, you touch me with those hands
and I'll rip you apart. No!

681
01:02:44.511 --> 01:02:46.554
No, look at them! No!

682
01:02:46.888 --> 01:02:48.431
No! No!

683
01:02:49.182 --> 01:02:49.766
No!

684
01:03:05.699 --> 01:03:07.993
May told me about the little beach
down by the trees.

685
01:03:08.159 --> 01:03:09.869
- Hm?
- Do you want to come?

686
01:03:10.537 --> 01:03:11.246
Love to.

687
01:03:12.080 --> 01:03:13.540
Except that I've gotta fix the fan belt,

688
01:03:13.707 --> 01:03:15.041
or we're never gonna get out of here.

689
01:03:16.334 --> 01:03:19.004
Okay, Tarzan,
I'll bring you back some bananas.

690
01:03:19.504 --> 01:03:20.171
Do that.

691
01:03:32.976 --> 01:03:33.643
Oi!

692
01:03:53.830 --> 01:03:54.706
Jessie.

693
01:03:56.374 --> 01:03:58.960
If you meet Benno down there,
don't let him trouble you.

694
01:03:59.294 --> 01:04:00.295
He's only a baby.

695
01:04:02.255 --> 01:04:03.048
Sure, May.

696
01:07:50.400 --> 01:07:51.067
The men.

697
01:07:52.193 --> 01:07:53.152
What men?
Come on.

698
01:07:53.695 --> 01:07:55.321
Now you calm down
and you tell me what's the matter.

699
01:07:55.738 --> 01:07:57.490
Very, very naughty.

700
01:07:58.074 --> 01:07:59.033
Now, you tell May--

701
01:07:59.200 --> 01:08:00.368
- May.
- ...what you...

702
01:08:00.952 --> 01:08:03.830
May, you call The Dark One.

703
01:08:04.289 --> 01:08:07.041
And you tell him to get here
as fast as he can.

704
01:08:07.375 --> 01:08:08.418
Why? What's going on?

705
01:08:08.585 --> 01:08:09.669
I think we've got some hoon trouble.

706
01:08:09.836 --> 01:08:11.546
- Oh.
- It's gonna be all right.

707
01:08:12.672 --> 01:08:14.674
Come on, darling. Come on, Jessie.

708
01:08:14.841 --> 01:08:17.051
Well, let's go into the house, huh?

709
01:08:17.677 --> 01:08:18.636
Come on.

710
01:08:30.273 --> 01:08:33.526
You've had an awful time, darling.

711
01:08:34.527 --> 01:08:36.404
But it's all over now.

712
01:08:37.572 --> 01:08:40.116
Everything's gonna be all right.

713
01:08:45.538 --> 01:08:47.582
I've just got to go and make a phone call

714
01:08:48.333 --> 01:08:50.835
and then we'll have
a nice hot cup of tea, eh?

715
01:09:09.646 --> 01:09:12.940
The Dark One, and hurry it up, will you?

716
01:09:13.524 --> 01:09:14.901
It's May Swaisey.

717
01:09:22.950 --> 01:09:25.536
Sprog? Oh, no!

718
01:09:35.338 --> 01:09:36.381
Sprog?

719
01:09:40.259 --> 01:09:41.302
Sprog!

720
01:09:46.057 --> 01:09:47.058
Sprog!

721
01:09:55.566 --> 01:09:56.567
Sprog!

722
01:10:05.034 --> 01:10:06.285
Sprog!

723
01:10:08.788 --> 01:10:12.208
Well, well, well.

724
01:10:13.626 --> 01:10:15.002
It's our little mother.

725
01:10:19.382 --> 01:10:21.884
That there is Cundalini

726
01:10:22.218 --> 01:10:25.221
and Cundalini wants his hand back.

727
01:10:27.849 --> 01:10:28.641
I want my baby.

728
01:10:29.225 --> 01:10:29.851
Tell you what,

729
01:10:32.437 --> 01:10:33.146
I'll swap you.

730
01:10:34.564 --> 01:10:36.774
Please, give me my baby.

731
01:10:37.150 --> 01:10:37.942
Jessie.

732
01:10:39.360 --> 01:10:41.279
Jessie, Jessie.

733
01:10:42.113 --> 01:10:44.449
You've not got a sense of humor.

734
01:10:45.867 --> 01:10:47.160
You've got a pretty face, though.

735
01:10:48.286 --> 01:10:49.537
Awful pretty.

736
01:10:50.621 --> 01:10:51.873
Awful pretty.

737
01:10:53.082 --> 01:10:56.294
I suppose you don't need
a sense of humor with a pretty face.

738
01:10:57.837 --> 01:10:59.213
The only trouble is though, missy,

739
01:11:00.381 --> 01:11:01.132
if you should...

740
01:11:03.509 --> 01:11:04.927
lose the face...

741
01:11:05.511 --> 01:11:06.679
Please, don't hurt my baby.

742
01:11:06.929 --> 01:11:08.181
You've got nothing!

743
01:11:08.473 --> 01:11:09.891
What do you want from me?

744
01:11:11.058 --> 01:11:14.103
- Don't change the subject.
- Hold it!

745
01:11:15.354 --> 01:11:16.564
- Right there!
- Ahh!

746
01:11:17.648 --> 01:11:19.233
Ah! I hate guns.

747
01:11:19.567 --> 01:11:20.359
Old lady.

748
01:11:20.902 --> 01:11:21.736
Stand back!

749
01:11:22.278 --> 01:11:23.196
Stay back!

750
01:11:23.946 --> 01:11:24.655
Woman!

751
01:11:24.822 --> 01:11:25.656
Stay back!

752
01:11:33.915 --> 01:11:38.085
Anyone so much as breathes,
I'll cheese him!

753
01:11:38.961 --> 01:11:39.879
Open that door.

754
01:11:40.463 --> 01:11:42.089
Every one of you, in there.

755
01:11:44.967 --> 01:11:46.552
Put the babe on the ground.

756
01:11:50.264 --> 01:11:52.099
Jessie, get the van.

757
01:12:31.806 --> 01:12:34.475
Don't stop. Just go right through it.

758
01:12:58.374 --> 01:12:59.458
Oh, now what?

759
01:13:07.508 --> 01:13:09.510
- The motor!
- What are you trying to say?

760
01:13:09.677 --> 01:13:11.095
I don't know, it just died on me!

761
01:13:12.972 --> 01:13:15.016
Get out. Run!

762
01:13:38.873 --> 01:13:39.540
Oh!

763
01:14:01.646 --> 01:14:02.355
Jessie!

764
01:14:03.689 --> 01:14:04.899
- Where? Where?
- Jess.

765
01:14:06.484 --> 01:14:08.027
Lord, have mercy!

766
01:14:09.654 --> 01:14:10.321
Lord!

767
01:14:54.782 --> 01:14:55.366
What do you reckon?

768
01:14:56.075 --> 01:14:58.035
Jesus, I'm a doctor, not a fortuneteller.

769
01:14:58.786 --> 01:14:59.620
This your subdural?

770
01:14:59.787 --> 01:15:00.621
Yes, that's her.

771
01:15:01.330 --> 01:15:02.206
Lot of problems, huh?

772
01:15:02.456 --> 01:15:06.043
Multiple traumas, spleen,
liver, lung, flail chest,

773
01:15:06.377 --> 01:15:08.337
left neck of femur, renal shutdown.

774
01:15:08.838 --> 01:15:11.382
Reads like a grocery list.
She salvageable?

775
01:15:11.549 --> 01:15:13.467
Yeah, sure, we got
all her signs back last night.

776
01:15:14.593 --> 01:15:16.220
- Relatives?
- The husband.

777
01:15:16.554 --> 01:15:18.347
They lost their kid. DOA.

778
01:15:19.098 --> 01:15:21.100
Listen, tell him
she's going to be all right.

779
01:15:21.767 --> 01:15:22.810
Tell him not to worry.

780
01:15:22.977 --> 01:15:24.937
Tell him if he wants, I'll talk to him.

781
01:15:25.813 --> 01:15:27.982
I don't think he wants to talk to anyone.

782
01:15:29.275 --> 01:15:31.277
He's been standing there
like a zombie all day.

783
01:16:34.757 --> 01:16:35.883
Bubba Zanetti, that you?

784
01:16:37.760 --> 01:16:38.761
You come for the grunt?

785
01:16:40.346 --> 01:16:41.972
She won't be ready till this afternoon.

786
